<chapter role="topic" id="service-quotas">
    <info>
        <title id="service-quotas.title">&MESH; service quotas</title>
        <titleabbrev>Service quotas</titleabbrev>
    </info>
    <para region="IAD;SEA">&MESHlong; has integrated with &SQlong;, an &AWS; service that enables
        you to view and manage your quotas from a central location. Service quotas are also referred
        to as limits. For more information, see <ulink type="documentation"
            url="servicequotas/latest/userguide/intro.html">What Is Service Quotas?</ulink> in the
        <emphasis>&guide-sq-user;</emphasis>.</para>
    <para region="IAD;SEA">&SQlong; makes it easy to look up the value of all of the &MESH; service
        quotas.</para>
    <procedure region="IAD;SEA">
        <title>To view &MESH; service quotas using the &console;</title>
        <step>&SQconsole_switch;</step>
        <step>
            <para>In the navigation pane, choose <guilabel>&AWS; services</guilabel>.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>From the <guilabel>&AWS; services</guilabel> list, search for and select
                <guilabel>&MESHlong;</guilabel>.</para>
            <para>In the <guilabel>Service quotas</guilabel> list, you can see the service quota
                name, applied value (if it is available), &AWS; default quota, and whether the quota
                value is adjustable.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>To view additional information about a service quota, such as the description,
                choose the quota name.</para>
        </step>
    </procedure>
    <para region="IAD;SEA">To request a quota increase, see <ulink type="documentation"
        url="servicequotas/latest/userguide/request-increase.html">Requesting a Quota
        Increase</ulink> in the <emphasis>&guide-sq-user;</emphasis>.</para>
    <formalpara region="IAD;SEA">
        <title>To view &MESH; service quotas using the &CLI;</title>
        <para>Run the following command.</para>
    </formalpara>
    <programlisting><userinput>aws service-quotas list-aws-default-service-quotas \
    --query 'Quotas[*].{Adjustable:Adjustable,Name:QuotaName,Value:Value,Code:QuotaCode}' \
    --service-code appmesh \
    --output table</userinput></programlisting>
    <para>To work more with service quotas using the &CLI;, see the <ulink type="documentation"
            url="cli/latest/reference/service-quotas/index.html#cli-aws-service-quotas">&SQ; &CLI;
            Command Reference</ulink>. </para>
    
    
